<h1 class="ui dividing header">
  Highlights
</h1>

<h3 class="ui header blue"> 
  Team Project Management 
</h3>
<p class="sub header">
  TeamTat makes it easy for managing a team annotation project 
  by allowing the annotation manager to conveniently distribute 
  annotation workload to a group of individuals and to collect, 
  and merge individual annotations.  
  <br>  <br>

  <%=link_to image_tag("sm_screenshot01.png", style: "width: 33%; border: 1px solid gray"), image_url("screenshot01.png"), class: "figure-box js-smartPhoto", data: {caption: "You can upload documents in any format such as BioC, text and XML, or import from PubMed and PubMed Central."} %>
  <%=link_to image_tag("sm_screenshot02.png", style: "width: 33%; border: 1px solid gray"), image_url("screenshot02.png"), class: "figure-box js-smartPhoto", data: {caption: "A project manager can invite annotator(s) to work on a given project."} %>
  <%=link_to image_tag("sm_screenshot03.png", style: "width: 33%; border: 1px solid gray"), image_url("screenshot03.png"), class: "figure-box js-smartPhoto", data: {caption: "Document assignment can be done manually, or automatically. Documents can also be assigned offline and uploaded."} %>
</p>

<h3 class="ui header blue" style="margin-top: 2em;"> 
  Streamlined Annotation Interface
</h3>
<p class="sub header">
  TeamTat allows each annotator to work independently and provides visual 
  clues when comparing results with another annotator. 
  TeamTat also supports many user-desired annotation functions 
  such as ability to annotate both entities and relations, 
  pre-annotation, inter-annotator agreement, etc.
  <br> <br>
  <%=link_to image_tag("sm_screenshot04.png", style: "width: 49%; border: 1px solid gray"), image_url("screenshot04.png"), class: "figure-box js-smartPhoto", data: {caption: "You can annotate directly on text with annotation type, concept ID, etc. Multi-label annotatoions are also supported."} %>
  <%=link_to image_tag("sm_screenshot05.png", style: "width: 49%; border: 1px solid gray"), image_url("screenshot05.png"), class: "figure-box js-smartPhoto", data: {caption: "Relation annotation is document level and entities can appear on different sentences, paragraphs, or sections. "} %>
</p>

<h3 class="ui header blue" style="margin-top: 2em;"> 
  Full Text Annotation with Figures 
</h3>
<p class="sub header">
  Users can annotate documents of any length, including full text journal articles, 
  in multiple data formats. TeamTat interface can display all 
  figures of full-text articles in PubMed Central. 
  <br>
  <br>
  <%=link_to image_tag("sm_screenshot06.png", style: "width: 49%; border: 1px solid gray"), image_url("screenshot06.png"), class: "figure-box js-smartPhoto", data: {caption: "If an article is retrieved from PubMed Central, TeamTat can display all images in text, for annotators’ convenience."} %>
  <%=link_to image_tag("sm_screenshot07.png", style: "width: 49%; border: 1px solid gray"), image_url("screenshot07.png"), class: "figure-box js-smartPhoto", data: {caption: "If an article is retrieved from PubMed Central, TeamTat can display all images in text, for annotators’ convenience."} %>
</p>

